entries.title: Biotech Venture Financing Market Remains Tight
entries.description: Biotechnology entrepreneurs early this year hoped for venture investment in their industry to recover. They’re still waiting.

entries.title: Why Lululemon's Stock Is Going Out of Fashion
entries.description: As it expands beyond yoga, the company’s growth is slowing in its key market and it faces tough competition.

entries.title: Biden Joins Allies to Remember D-Day Landings in a Turbulent World
entries.description: Western leaders will mark the 80th anniversary of the D-Day landings as anxieties run high over the war in Ukraine and the future of trans-Atlantic relations.

entries.title: KKR, GIP, Indo-Pacific Group Form $25 Billion Regional Infrastructure Tie-Up
entries.description: A coalition of investors, led by private-equity firms KKR and Global Infrastructure Partners, as well as the Indo-Pacific Partnership for Prosperity, has pledged to invest $25 billion in infrastructure in the Indo-Pacific region.

entries.title: CrowdStrike CEO, DOJ Official and Executives to Take the Stage
entries.description: National security threats, the impact of AI and so-called pig-butchering scams are on the agenda for the daylong event.

entries.title: Chinese Battery Suppliers Tied to Ford, VW Should Be Banned, GOP Lawmakers Say
entries.description: A group of lawmakers call for CATL and Gotion to be added to an import ban list over alleged forced labor in their supply chains.

entries.title: Meta's AI Project Faces Privacy Complaints in Europe
entries.description: Meta’s new artificial-intelligence project faces complaints from a privacy-focused advocacy group in eleven European countries, highlighting the challenges for big technology as it turns to users’ data to train its AI tools.

entries.title: Hannon's Take: U.S. Government Debt Is A Growing Concern
entries.description: The changing outlook for the Federal Reserve’s key interest rate has been a preoccupation for many policymakers around the world this year. But another concern about the U.S. economy is on the rise — the large and fast-growing government debt.

entries.title: Executives and Officials Convene at WSJ Tech Live: Cybersecurity
entries.description: National security threats, the impact of AI and so-called pig-butchering scams are on the agenda for the daylong event.

entries.title: The 'Mind-Boggling' Hockey Star Finally Getting His Stanley Cup Showcase
entries.description: Connor McDavid has done almost everything—besides win a Stanley Cup. Now a generational talent will lead Edmonton against favored Florida.

entries.title: Keith Gill's GameStop Trades Pose Conundrum for Market Cops
entries.description: Lawyers say it is unlikely regulators could bring a case against the meme-stock influencer based on the facts currently known about his trading.

entries.title: Get Ready for NBA Players to Make $100 Million a Year
entries.description: America’s star athletes are on their way to nine-figure salaries. And it might happen sooner than you think.

entries.title: Stellantis-Mercedes JV's Pivot to Cheaper Batteries Looks Smart
entries.description: The battery-making JV owned by Stellantis, Mercedes-Benz, and TotalEnergies is refocusing its strategy—and its money—on building cheaper batteries in a move that makes sense given underwhelming EV demand, Citi said.

entries.title: Israel Strikes U.N. School and Shelter in Gaza, Says Hamas Was Operating There
entries.description: Palestinian officials said dozens of displaced people were killed at the facility in central Gaza.

entries.title: U.K. Businesses See Wage Rises Slowing, BOE Survey Finds
entries.description: U.K. businesses expect wages to rise at a slower pace over the coming 12 months, a finding that will help reassure policymakers at the Bank of England that inflation has been tamed.

entries.title: Remy Martin Sees Tough Year Ahead as U.S. Slowdown Drags on
entries.description: Remy Cointreau expects efforts to clear out excess inventory in the U.S. to stretch into its new fiscal year amid a market slowdown, as the company seeks to pave the way for a return to sales growth.

entries.title: Oil Rebounds From Four-Month Lows Despite Demand Concerns
entries.description: Oil prices rebounded from four-month lows as market watchers viewed the recent sell-off as overdone, despite an unexpected build in U.S. crude and gasoline inventories.

entries.title: Antofagasta Secures Water Supply for Key Mine
entries.description: Antofagasta shares opened higher on London’s FTSE 100, on news the copper miner had signed a water-supply pact at its flagship Centinela site in Chile.

entries.title: Sterling Traders Await BOE Survey
entries.description: Sterling traded steady as markets awaited the Bank of England’s decision maker panel’s survey at 0830 GMT with information on inflation expectations, Brown Brothers Harriman said.

entries.title: Gold Futures Rise, Reclaiming Losses From Selloff in Late May
entries.description: Gold futures rose, further reclaiming ground lost in late May, and MUFG reiterated gold is its favorite buy this year on a trifecta of eventual Fed cuts, supportive central bank demand and its role as a geopolitical safe haven.
